      "content": "I hear the immense weight of feeling like a house with no one inside, and the exhaustion of maintaining a vessel when the spark seems lost. It is completely natural to feel that survival is pointless when the part of you that once felt real has faded away. You are not alone in this darkness, and there are people who want to walk with you through it, even if the path feels steep and lonely.",
